RootCauseAnalysis - INFO -     Result: {'result': 'Looking at the trace data, I can see two distinct issues occurring simultaneously:\n\n1. **ShippingService Unavailability**: The error traces show consistent "i/o timeout" and "timed out waiting for server handshake" errors when checkoutservice tries to connect to shippingservice (port 50051). This is causing checkout failures with HTTP 500 errors.\n\n2. **Redis Latency Anomalies**: The initial analysis showed extreme latency in redis HGET operations (77555.0 vs normal ~1740 microseconds) and cartservice operations (78209.0 vs normal ~2500 microseconds).\n\nHowever, looking at the actual HGET traces returned, I notice all the durations are in the normal range (444-3690 microseconds), not the extreme 77555.0 microseconds mentioned in the initial analysis. This suggests the extreme latency spike was a brief anomaly that may have resolved or occurred outside the sampled traces.\n\nThe most consistent and severe issue is the ShippingService being completely unavailable, causing a cascade of failures throughout the checkout process. The error messages indicate connection timeouts, suggesting the shippingservice is either down or unreachable.\n\n```json\n{\n  "detected_trace_keys": ["error_ratio", "checkoutservice->shippingservice", "deadline_exceeded", "connection_timeout"],\n  "affected_components": ["shippingservice", "checkoutservice", "frontend"],\n  "missing_traces": [],\n  "trace_summary": "Primary root cause is shippingservice unavailability causing checkout failures. Multiple traces show \'i/o timeout\' and \'timed out waiting for server handshake\' errors when checkoutservice attempts to connect to shippingservice on port 50051. This results in HTTP 500 errors propagating to frontend. While initial analysis indicated extreme redis latency anomalies, the actual HGET operations in sampled traces show normal durations, suggesting the latency spike was transient.",\n  "next_verification": {\n    "action": "check_pod_status",\n    "reason": "Shippingservice appears completely unreachable with consistent connection timeouts, indicating the service pod may be down or crashed",\n    "suggested_metrics": ["pod_ready_status", "container_restart_count"],\n    "suggested_log_keywords": ["shippingservice", "OOMKilled", "crash", "exit"]\n  }\n}\n```'}
